                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2480: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-03T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1919, noon</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to Department’s October 3, 6 p.m. and your despatch No. 2980 of
                    September 3, American Group informs Department that next payment of interest
                    coupons on Hukuang loan falls due December 15th when question of status of
                    German issue will again arise. It is desired that you report immediately as to
                    the nature and result of Legation’s representations to the Chinese Government in
                    this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
